1801 (Thomas Young) interference experiment, or double-slit experiment
1818 (Augustin-Jean Fresnel) published his Memoir on the Diffraction of Light
1865 (James Clerk Maxwell) proposed that light is an undulation in the same medium that is the cause of electric and magnetic phenomena
